<item>
            <title>[LU-18897] NULL pointer dereference when handling RDMA_CM_EVENT_UNREACHABLE with no context</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18897</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In kiblnd_cm_callback, when we handle a RDMA_CM_EVENT_UNREACHABLE, we read cmid-&amp;gt;context fields. But in some cases, the pointer can be NULL. We should handle this scenario, and check if we can have similar cases for other types of events.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
